Sentencas: Co-Substituted Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (Sr2Fe1.3Co0.2Mo0.5O6-delta) double perovskite oxides have been prepared and evaluated as anode materials of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Co-substituted Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells: Achieving high performance via nanoparticle exsolution

Sentencas: In reducing atmosphere, active cobalt metal nanoparticles are in situ exsolved from the parent double perovskite oxides, which are characterized by XRD, XPS, SEM and TEM.
Titulo: Co-substituted Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells: Achieving high performance via nanoparticle exsolution

Sentencas: Sr2Fe1.3Co0.2Mo0.5O6-delta show the highest electrical conductivity of 13.9 S cm(-1) at 600 degrees C and the lowest polarization resistance of 0.15 Omega cm(2) at 850 degrees C in 5% H-2-95% N-2.
Titulo: Co-substituted Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells: Achieving high performance via nanoparticle exsolution

Sentencas: When hydrogen, syngas and methane are filled as fuel, a maximum power density of 1.09, 0.981 and 0.29 W cm(-2) could be achieved at 850 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Co-substituted Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells: Achieving high performance via nanoparticle exsolution

Sentencas: Further, after continuously operated in hydrogen for 115 hs, in syngas for 190 hs and in methane for 300 hs, there are no negligible degradations.
Titulo: Co-substituted Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells: Achieving high performance via nanoparticle exsolution

Sentencas: Synergistic effect between perovskite oxide and exsolved Co nanoparticles contributes to the improved SOFCs performances.
Titulo: Co-substituted Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells: Achieving high performance via nanoparticle exsolution

Sentencas: The protocol developed in this research provides a new strategy to optimize anodic activities of double perovskite oxides, and broadens our horizons in rational design of heterogeneous ceramics for other applications.
Titulo: Co-substituted Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells: Achieving high performance via nanoparticle exsolution
